-- Italy Hires Citi, IMI, Deutsche, Nomura, RBS for 15-Year Bond Syndication
-- B y   A n d r e w   D a v i s
-- 2010-09-21T13:56:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-21/italy-hires-citigroup-other-banks-to-sell-new-15-year-bond.html
The Italian Treasury said it hired
Banca IMI SpA, Citigroup Global Markets Ltd., Deutsche Bank AG,
Nomura Bank International Plc and Royal Bank of Scotland Plc to
syndicate a new benchmark 15-year bond.  The bond will mature in March 2026, the Treasury said in an
e-mailed statement. Details of the sales will be announced in
the near future based on market conditions, the statement said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Davis at 
 abdavis@bloomberg.net  